#: ../../source/user_guide/concepts.rst:2 5b38ad7aab8842559db887601bec4de2
msgid "Concepts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/concepts.rst:4 4f85b83c791845e8924fedd01397a930
msgid ""
"TensorMesh is a finite-element library written from the ground up for "
"PyTorch. A :class:`~tensormesh.Mesh` is an :class:`torch.nn.Module`, weak"
" forms are plain ``forward`` methods that receive basis tensors, and "
"every linear solve is a differentiable op. The same code that solves a "
"Poisson problem on a laptop CPU also runs on a GPU and backpropagates "
"through to a learnable parameter — without changing the FEM logic."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/concepts.rst:12 8166a7f4cb704b9caad25aa9f2456440
msgid ""
"This page is the mental model: how the modules fit together and the "
"design principles behind those choices."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/concepts.rst:17 ddb2c87e6c0d4f5287d574f9d80f0cd9
msgid "The FEM workflow"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/concepts.rst:19 47ec64cc5eb6460fba3b961c454fa388
msgid "Solving a PDE in TensorMesh follows one canonical pipeline:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/concepts.rst:25 222f30de54074c578e2ddaa1ab1fffa1
msgid "**Mesh** discretizes the domain into points and cells."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/concepts.rst:26 7ea961fd427146d0adf22c56d1dd03fb
msgid ""
"**Assembler** turns a weak form (``a(u, v)`` or ``l(v)``) into a "
":class:`~tensormesh.sparse.SparseMatrix` or load vector."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/concepts.rst:28 e1c1f30845af4f60b8997dfa38714ce6
msgid ""
"**Condenser** applies Dirichlet boundary conditions by static "
"condensation, producing a reduced system on the interior DOFs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/concepts.rst:30 52275ce56bf843eda4207c787a688a80
msgid ""
"**Solve** dispatches the reduced system to a sparse-linear-algebra "
"backend (via the :doc:`torch-sla <linear_solvers>` package)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/concepts.rst:33 fb026b6e6d1545e382992f2db841c2e8
msgid ""
"The :doc:`../getting_started/quickstart` walks through this pipeline end-"
"to-end in about 30 lines of Python. Each subsequent chapter of this guide"
" zooms in on one stage."
msgstr ""

